ef%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-steve-wozniak-salary-50-per-week-after-tax-report-2020-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESteve%20Wozniak%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Markkula%20approached%20Scott%20as%20he%20believed%20Jobs%20and%20Wozniak%20to%20be%20too%20inexperienced%20to%20lead%20Apple.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScott's%20tenure%20as%20CEO%20ended%20following%20an%20incident%20on%20February%2025%2C%201981%2C%20that%20has%20come%20to%20be%20known%20as%20%26quot%3BBlack%20Wednesday%2C%26quot%3B%20in%20which%20he%20abruptly%20fired%2040%20employees.%20Later%20that%20day%2C%20over%20a%20keg%20of%20beer%2C%20Scott%20proclaimed%20that%20he%20would%20continue%20to%20fire%20employees%20whenever%20being%20CEO%20wasn't%20%26quot%3Bfun%26quot%3B%20anymore%20and%20only%20stop%20when%20his%20mood%20improved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMike%20Markkula%20(1981-1983)%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-cofounder-mark-markkula-california-ranch-photos-2020-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMike%20Markkula%3C%2Fa%3E%20personally%20invested%20more%20than%20%2490%2C000%20in%20Apple%20and%20managed%20to%20secure%20the%20company%20a%20line%20of%20credit%20worth%20%24250%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMarkkula%20replaced%20Michael%20Scott%20following%20the%20%26quot%3BBlack%20Wednesday%26quot%3B%20incident%2C%20the%20fallout%20of%20which%20saw%20Scott%20relegated%20to%20vice%20chair%20of%20the%20board%20of%20directors.%20Markkula%20served%20as%20Apple's%20chairman%20from%201985%20until%201997.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMarkkula%20approved%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-apple-macintosh-bill-gates-steve-jobs-2018-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoriginal%20Macintosh%3C%2Fa%3E%20project%20in%201979%20and%20defended%20it%20against%20Jobs'%20desire%20to%20cancel%20it%20in%20favor%20of%20his%20Lisa%20project.%20When%20Markkula%20went%20against%20Jobs%20in%20a%20dispute%2C%20Jobs%20ultimately%20left%20Apple.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Markkula%20was%20later%20instrumental%20in%20ousting%20John%20Sculley%20as%20CEO%20in%201993%20and%20naming%20Jobs%20CEO%20in%201997.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EJohn%20Sculley%20(1983-1993)%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EJohn%20Sculley%20became%20the%20chief%20executive%20of%20PepsiCo%20in%201977%2C%20where%20he%20launched%20the%20wildly%20successful%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpepsi-challenge-business-insider-2013-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EPepsi%20Challenge%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20usurping%20Coca-Cola%20as%20America's%20number%20one%20soft%20drink%20pick.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Steve%20Jobs%20and%20John%20Sculley%20lean%20on%20original%20Apple%20computers%2C%20Lisa%20and%20Macintosh%2C%20in%20a%20black%20and%20white%20photo%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6582c7b0a79e5746976b6819%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221326%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESteve%20Jobs%2C%20left%2C%20and%20John%20Sculley.%20Sculley%20is%20leaning%20on%20the%20Apple%20%26quot%3BLisa%26quot%3B%20personal%20computer%20which%20succeeded%20the%20original%20Macintosh%2C%20on%20which%20Jobs%20is%20leaning.%3Cp%3EMediaNews%20Group%2FThe%20Mercury%20News%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESculley%20took%20the%20reins%20of%20Apple%20after%20being%20convinced%20to%20leave%20PepsiCo%20by%20Steve%20Jobs.%20Jobs%20posed%20the%20question%20%26quot%3BDo%20you%20want%20to%20sell%20sugared%20water%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20your%20life%3F%20Or%20do%20you%20want%20to%20come%20with%20me%20and%20change%20the%20world%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20timing%20of%20this%20could%20not%20have%20been%20better%2C%20given%20Mike%20Markkula's%20desire%20to%20re-enter%20retirement.%20While%20Jobs%20had%20wanted%20to%20take%20over%20as%20company%20president%2C%20Markkula%20feared%20that%20he%20still%20lacked%20the%20experience%20and%20temperament%20to%20lead%20Apple.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFollowing%20a%20string%20of%20product%20flops%2C%20Sculley%20was%20replaced%20in%201993%20at%20the%20direction%20of%20the%20board%20of%20directors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMichael%20Spindler%20(1993-1996)%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMichael%20Spindler%20was%20initially%20recruited%20to%20Apple%20by%20Mike%20Makkula%20with%20the%20goal%20of%20helping%20its%20European%20presence.%20Prior%20to%20becoming%20Apple%20CEO%2C%20he%20was%20the%20company's%20Chief%20Operating%20Officer.%20Under%20his%20tenure%2C%20Apple%20went%20through%20a%20major%20restructuring%20and%20launched%20a%20mixed%20portfolio%20of%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223648%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Michael%20Spindler%20stands%20in%20front%20of%20computer%20monitors%20and%20keyboards%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6582c831a79e5746976b6834%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222395%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMichael%20Spindler.%3Cp%3EWilliam%20Stevens%2FGamma-Rapho%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESpindler%20was%20at%20the%20helm%20for%20the%20successful%20launch%20of%20Apple's%20PowerPC%20product%20line.%20In%201994%20he%20led%20Apple%20into%20a%20partnership%20with%20IBM%20and%20Motorola%2C%20forming%20the%20AIM%20alliance%20with%20the%20goal%20of%20achieving%20a%20dominant%20position%20as%20the%20primary%20computer%20operating%20system%2C%20a%20title%20still%20held%20by%20Microsoft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20success%20of%20the%20alliance%2C%20Apple%20allowed%20Motorola%20and%20others%20to%20make%20clones%20of%20the%20Macintosh%3B%20two%20years%20later%2C%2075%20clones%20had%20been%20made.%20This%20ultimately%20concerned%20Apple%20that%20it%20could%20jeopardize%20sales%20of%20its%20own%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EGilbert%20Frank%20Amelio%20(1996-1997)%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGilbert%20Frank%20Amelio%20was%20hired%20as%20CEO%20by%20the%20board.%20Prior%20t