20days%2C%20following%20which%20he%20managed%20to%20switch%20on%20the%20phone%20after%20connecting%20a%20charger.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20iPhone%2012%20comes%20with%20an%20IP68%20rating.%20According%20to%20Apple%2C%20the%20phone%20can%20last%2030%20minutes%20in%206-meter%20deep%20water.%20However%2C%20this%20one%20iPhone%20unit%20seems%20to%20be%20breaking%20the%20rules%20as%20it%20managed%20to%20remain%20functional%20even%20after%20being%20submerged%20in%20water%20for%20over%203%20months.%20Speaking%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fappleinsider.com%2Farticles%2F23%2F12%2F19%2Falgae-covered-iphone-12-recovered-from-3-month-dip-in-river-still-works%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EApple%20Insider%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Lee%20shared%20his%20story%20of%20the%20discovery%20and%20revealed%20how%20he%20successfully%20managed%20to%20switch%20on%20the%20phone.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELee%20discovered%20the%20mobile%20treasure%20while%20cleaning%20the%20Stanislaus%20River%20on%20November%2010%20and%20after%20drying%20the%20phone%2C%20he%20switched%20on%20the%20device%20after%20connecting%20it%20to%20a%20charger.%20The%20diver%20revealed%20that%20the%20phone%20lacked%20a%20passcode%20or%20face%20unlock%20setup%20due%20to%20which%20he%20was%20able%20to%20unlock%20it%20and%20access%20its%20stored%20data.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELee%20told%20the%20outlet%20that%20the%20most%20recent%20item%20in%20the%20Photos%20app%20was%20a%20video%20captured%20on%20the%20river%20on%20September%204%2C%20suggesting%20that%20it%20had%20been%20submerged%20there%20for%20three%20months.%20He%20stated%20that%20he%20hasn't%20been%20able%20to%20get%20in%20touch%20with%20the%20owner%20of%20the%20iPhone%20but%20plans%20to%20reach%20out%20to%20the%20contacts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlso%20read%20%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Fthis-is-the-most-deleted-app-of-2023-the-name-is-4727714%5C%22%3EThis%20Is%20The%20Most%20Deleted%20App%20Of%202023.%20The%20Name%20Is..