C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I'm%20a%20pro%20poker%20player%20and%20believe%20learning%20the%20game%20can%20help%20women%20like%20myself%20excel%20in%20a%20male-dominated%20workplace.%20Here's%20my%20advice.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221673%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Abby%20Merk%20holds%20up%20her%20winnings%20after%20a%20poker%20game.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6584a1b41c5c7b8c9a0b4c10%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221255%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAbby%20Merk%20holds%20up%20her%20winnings%20after%20a%20poker%20game.%3Cp%3EAJ%20Rudolph%2FCourtesy%20of%20Abby%20Merk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAbby%20Merk%2C%2023%2C%20learned%20to%20play%20poker%20three%20years%20ago.%20She's%20already%20gone%20pro.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20now%20can%20earn%20more%20than%20%2411%2C000%20in%20a%20single%20game.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe's%20an%20instructor%20at%20Poker%20Power%2C%20a%20company%20that%20teaches%20women%20workplace%20skills%20through%20poker.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Abby%20Merk%2C%20a%2023-year-old%20poker%20player%2C%20instructor%2C%20and%20content%20creator.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20first%20started%20learning%20to%20play%20poker%20about%20three%20years%20ago%2C%20I%20thought%20there%20was%20more%20luck%20involved.%20I%20thought%20it%20was%20gambling.%20But%20once%20you%20dive%20into%20poker%2C%20you%20understand%20there's%20always%20a%20correct%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20a%20losing%20player%20at%20first.%20We%20all%20start%20there.%20As%20soon%20as%20I%20fell%20in%20love%20with%20the%20game%20and%20started%20studying%20it%20on%20my%20own%2C%20I%20realized%20I%20was%20not%20unlucky%20%E2%80%94%20I%20was%20just%20making%20mathematically%20incorrect%20decisions.%20To%20think%20like%20a%20poker%20player%2C%20you%20have%20to%20change%20how%20you%20think%20about%20the%20game%20and%20start%20to%20see%20those%20patterns%2C%20and%20that%20only%20comes%20with%20reps.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20studied%20philosophy%20and%20mathematics%20at%20Wake%20Forest%20University.%20I%20fell%20in%20love%20with%20how%20philosophy%20got%20me%20to%20think%20about%20the%20world%2C%20and%20I%20fell%20in%20love%20with%20how%20math%20helped%20me%20analyze%20it.%20That's%20basically%20what%20you're%20doing%20in%20poker.%20You're%20thinking%20about%20the%20situations%20analytically%20and%20critically.%20You%20can%20use%20your%20people%20skills%20and%20how%20you%20think%20others%20might%20perceive%20the%20world%2C%20or%20in%20this%20case%2C%20the%20table%2C%20and%20then%20you%20can%20use%20mathematical%20skills%20to%20back%20your%20decisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20love%20the%20competitive%20nature%20of%20playing%20with%20other%20people%2C%20and%20if%20you%20can%20get%20good%20at%20something%20and%20make%20money%20doing%20it%2C%20that%20is%20something%20that%20piques%20my%20interest.%20The%20things%20that%20you'll%20gain%20by%20learning%20poker%20and%20understanding%20the%20game%20will%20be%20the%20same%20no%20matter%20where%20you%20go%20with%20it.%20The%20experiences%20that%20I%20was%20having%20at%20the%20%2420%20tables%2C%20I'm%20still%20having%20in%20the%20%2410%2C000%20events.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20known%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsue-wagner-muffy-macmillan-entrepreneurship-gender-gap-funding-wendy-daimond-2023-12%23jenny-just-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJenny%20Just%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgender-pay-equity-gap-teaching-women-girls-play-poker-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPoker%20Power%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20forever.%20She's%20been%20really%20good%20friends%20with%20my%20parents%20for%20a%20long%20time%2C%20and%20she%20was%20always%20a%20mentor%20for%20me.%20I%20was%20one%20of%20the%20first%20students%20of%20Poker%20Power%2C%20so%20I%20learned%20through%20them.%20At%20that%20point%2C%20their%20lessons%20were%20shorter%20and%20less%20in-depth.%20But%20I%20was%20able%20to%20take%20a%20few%20months%20and%20dive%20into%20the%20game.%20And%20I%20fell%20in%20love%20with%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20few%20months%2C%20I%20was%20playing%20for%20real%20money%20at%20tournaments.%20It%20was%20%2420%2C%20nothing%20crazy.%20But%20I%20was%20risking%20something%20tangible%20and%20taking%20my%20seat%20at%20the%20table.%20That%20was%20a%20pivotal%20moment%20for%20me%20because%20I%20faced%20a%20ton%20of%20backlash.%20When%20I%20sat%20down%20at%20the%20poker%20table%2C%20I%20was%20instantaneously%20stereotyped.%20My%20play%20was%20supposed%20to%20fall%20into%20a%20certain%20category%3B%20I%20was%20supposed%20to%20be%20tight%2C%20so%20I%20was%20not%20supposed%20to%20play%20a%20lot%20of%20hands%2C%20and%20I%20was%20supposed%20to%20be%20passive%20when%20I%20played%20them%20because%20I%20was%20a%20female.%20As%20soon%20as%20I%20realized%20that%20that's%20how%20they%20were%20stereotyping%20me%2C%20I%20took%20that%20to%20heart.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20played%20horribly.%20I%20remember%20this%20so%20distinctly.%20I%20thought%20I%20was%20so%20good%2C%20and%20I%20lost%20my%20first%20hand.%20This%20was%20pivotal%20for%20me%20because%20it%20got%20me%20to%20drop%20my%20ego%2C%20focus%20on%20what%20the%20game%20actually%20is%2C%20and%20stick%20up%20for%20myself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20remember%20after%20that%20hand%2C%20I%20went%20to%20rebuy%2C%20and%20while%20I%20was%20waiting%20in%20the%20line%2C%20this%20guy%20who%20was%20at%20the%20table%20came%20up%20to%20me%20and%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BJust%20so%20you%20know%2C%20that%20was%20a%20really%20bad%20decision%2C%20you%20know%2C%20right%3F%20That%20was%20a%20bad%20decision.%26quot%3B%20I%20replied%3A%20%26quot%3BWas%20it%20a%20bad%20decision%20or%20did%20it%20have%20a%20bad%20outcome%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20that's%20the%20key%20to%20poker%3A%20To%20flip%20that%20question%20back%20on%20others%20that%20might%20give%20you%20some%20adversity%20because%20if%20you%20can%20separate%20bad%20decisions%20from%20bad%20outcomes%2C%20you'll%20be%20a%20great%20poker%20player.%20That%20realization%20was%20something%20that%20transformed%20my%20poker%20career.%20Just%20knowing%20that%20I%20belong%20and%20that%20a%20random%20guy%20at%20a%20table%20playing%20a%20%2420%20tournament%20isn't%20going%20to%20dictate%20how%20I%20feel%20about%20myself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20studying.%20I%20kicked%20it%20into%20gear%20and%20started%20consuming%20as%20much%20poker%20content%20as%20I%20could.%20I%20became%20good%20enough%20to%20be%20a%20Poker%20Power%20teacher%2C%20and%20I%20felt%20confident%20in%20what%20I%20was%20saying%20because%20I%20had%20some%20results%20to%20back%20it%20up.%20I%20was%20able%20to%20start%20teaching%20other%20women%20to%20be%20in%20situations%20where%20they%20can%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BTo%20hell%20with%20all%20the%20other%20guys%20here.%20I'm%20going%20to%20take%20my%20seat.%20And%20I'm%20going%20to%20do%20well.%20And%20you%20guys%20can't%20do%20anything%20about%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20mindset%20and%20the%20game%20itself%20are%20helpful%20in%20any%20workplace%20environment%2C%20especially%20in%20finance.%20In%20a%20financial%20environment%2C%20you%20will%20be%20the%20minority%20as%20a%20woman.%20So%20I%20think%20having%20the%20confidence%20to%20make%20your%20voice%20heard%20challenges%20the%20status%20quo.%20Women%20existing%20in%20or%20striving%20for%20positions%20of%20power%20is%20sometimes%20an%20uncomfortable%20feeling%20for%20men%2C%20and%20the%20only%20way%20to%20get%20around%20that%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20only%20way%20to%20go%20against%20that%20%E2%80%94%20is%20to%20keep%20doing%20it%2C%20to%20keep%20putting%20yourself%20in%20situations%20where%20you%20can%20rise%20above.%20That's%20hard%20to%20do%