20couple%20of%20weeks%5D%2C%20some%20mainstream%20filmmakers%20hitting%20their%20stride%20again%2C%20and%20some%20of%20our%20most%20topical%20filmmakers%20finding%20a%20way%20to%20beat%20a%20system%20that%20quashes%20even%20the%20slightest%20hints%20of%20commentary.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHere%20are%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%98s%20picks%20for%20some%20of%20the%20best%20Hindi%20films%20that%20came%20out%20in%202023.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cb%3EJoram%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDevashish%20Makhija%E2%80%99s%20fourth%20feature%20as%20director%2C%20is%20the%20rare%20political%20film%20(in%20Hindi)%20that%20slipped%20through%20the%20fingers%20of%20a%20sensitive%20censor%20board.%20Twenty%20minutes%20shorter%20than%20its%20festival%20cut%2C%20the%20film%20follows%20a%20man%20(a%20very%20physical%20Manoj%20Bajpayee)%20from%20a%20tribal%20community%20in%20Jharkhand%2C%20whose%20land%20is%20usurped%20by%20a%20mining%20company%2C%20forcing%20him%20to%20join%20the%20Naxals%2C%20only%20to%20later%20flee%20to%20Mumbai%20where%20he%20works%20as%20a%20construction%20labourer.%20After%20being%20recognised%20by%20a%20local%20politician%20(Smita%20Tambe%2C%20who%20arguably%20had%20the%20highest%20impact%20to%20screen%20time%20ratio%20of%20the%20year)%20in%20Mumbai%2C%20who%20orders%20the%20murder%20of%20his%20wife%20and%20implicates%20him%20for%20it%2C%20the%20man%20is%20forced%20to%20flee%20with%20his%20three-month-old%20baby%20tied%20to%20his%20back.%20Sparingly%20written%20and%20evocatively%20shot%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EJoram%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20plays%20out%20like%20one%20of%20the%20most%20gruelling%20films%20of%20the%20year%20%E2%80%93%20where%20the%20marginalised%20find%20only%20injustice%20at%20various%20seemingly%20invisible%20junctures.%20Even%20after%20they%E2%80%99ve%20put%20their%20heads%20down%20and%20made%20peace%20with%20the%20oppressi